  <description><![CDATA[<p>Chalet Chloe is one of three chalets in a small residence at the entrance to the Balcons area of <a data-udi="umb://document/50690c0f70c74050930d18799cab6fa8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/50690c0f70c74050930d18799cab6fa8}" title="Val Thorens">Val Thorens</a>. The building is shared exclusively with Chalets <a data-udi="umb://document/65b4a42a6b4a41abbeb1d855ba97c925" href="/{localLink:umb://document/65b4a42a6b4a41abbeb1d855ba97c925}" title="Chalet Mathilde">Mathilde</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/66ca5d10cae64be8b9b5fb73ed58606d" href="/{localLink:umb://document/66ca5d10cae64be8b9b5fb73ed58606d}" title="Chalet Noella">Noella</a>. The entrance is on the top floor and a shared staircase leads to the chalets, which are each individually run and hosted. Chalet Chloe <span><span class="ui-provider a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z ab ac ae af ag ah ai aj ak">is available to book exclusively as well as room by room.</span></span></p>
<h2>Excellent location</h2>
<p>At 2,300 metres, Val Thorens is one of the highest resorts in Europe, and it is connected to the <a data-udi="umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578" href="/{localLink:umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578}" title="Three Valleys Ski Area">Three Valleys</a>, which is the largest lift-linked area, so skiers and snowboarders of all skill levels can enjoy excellent snow coverage and a variety of slopes. The Chalet Chloe is in an excellent location in Val Thorens, to access the Plein Sud blue, which runs through the village, head 100 metres along the road in the morning and ski directly to the lifts that connect to the Three Valleys, or turn right to descend to <a data-udi="umb://document/4eae720ba8984d83a83f530983b4b6f8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4eae720ba8984d83a83f530983b4b6f8}" title="Les Menuires">Les Menuires</a>.</p>
<p>The centre of the resort is only a five-minute walk away, where you'll find a wide range of shops, cafes, and restaurants. If you are having a day off of skiing, the resort has a range of facilities to keep you occupied including the new Le Board sport centre.</p>
<h2>Chalet catering</h2>
<p>Your chalet hosts will be there to help you with everything you might need throughout your holiday to ensure that you have an enjoyable time. The hosts prepare home-cooked comfort food, including a cooked breakfast, afternoon tea snacks, and a four-course dinner with wine, beer and soft drinks. On staff day off the hosts will leave a continental breakfast out and you are free to spend the evening however you'd like in resort. The hosts will, in addition to cooking and serving your meals, keep the chalet clean for the duration of your stay. Since you are on holiday, the only thing that is required of you is to get up and go skiing.</p>
<h2>Unwind and relax</h2>
<p>The interior of the chalet is styled in the classic Alpine style, and it features comfortable furnishings throughout the entire property, including a lounge and dining area that share an open layout. After spending the day exploring the Three Valleys, make your way back to the chalet to relax with a cup of coffee and a tasty treat for afternoon tea. Alternatively, you can soak up some winter sun on the sun terrace, which offers stunning views of the resort.</p>
<p>After a long day on the slopes, relax and rejuvenate in the wellness area including a sauna and steam room that is shared between guests in the residence.</p>
<h3>Why is this is an Inghams' Choice property?</h3>
<p><strong>Easy ski access</strong><span> </span>- Located a short walk away from the Plein Sud piste you have quick and easy access to the <a data-udi="umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578" href="/{localLink:umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578}" title="Three Valleys Ski Area">Three Valleys</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Close to resort</strong><span> </span>- Chalet Chloe is a short walk to the resort centre where you can find plenty of shops, restaurants and bars. There are also plenty of other non-skiing activities to keep you entertained including the state of the art Le Board sport centre. </p>
<p><strong>Chalet hosts -</strong> Our chalet hosts are on hand to make your stay enjoyable, look forward to freshly prepared meals and relax knowing the tidying up is done for you - after all you are on holiday.</p>
<h3>Our chalets are going greener so our mountains don't</h3>
<p><span>In all of our chalets we're giving you more choice, with both meat-free and meat options on offer throughout your stay. This is driven as part of our commitment to reduce our </span><a rel="noopener" data-udi="umb://document/67e40dbb55ff45098496ea2e7eee1f72" href="/{localLink:umb://document/67e40dbb55ff45098496ea2e7eee1f72}" target="_blank" title="Sustainability">carbon footprint</a><span>.</span></p>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-12">
